HEADWORD: Roadbed
<hw>Road"bed`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>In railroads, the
bed or foundation on which the superstructure (ties, rails, etc.) rests;
in common roads, the whole material laid in place and ready for
travel.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

